<task id="060" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-C-13 — Additive `workspace.*` PaneEventBus event types (reverse-flow workspace → assistant + context)</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <outcome-note>TS work landed via sub-agent before stream timeout at ~3.6h; main session closeout 2026-06-09 completed evidence note + POML + TASK-INDEX. 4 new variants on `WorkspacePaneEvent.type`: user_selection (200-char selectionText cap; user-visible-by-design per FR-38 + Pillar 9), tab_edited (editedFields = NAMES not values), tab_focused, tab_provenance_clicked. ADR-015 distinction (selectionText user-content vs telemetry-prohibited content on context.*) documented inline. Type-check 0 errors. ADR-030 4-channel preserved. Same pattern as task 034 (sub-agent timeout closeout from main session). Full evidence: notes/task-060-workspace-pane-events-evidence.md.</outcome-note>
    <estimated-effort>4 hours</estimated-effort>
    <phase>Phase C — Tri-directional Workspace (Pillar 6c)</phase>
    <wave>C-G2 (parallel after 6a)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>053 (workspace state wired)</dependencies>
    <tags>frontend, typescript, ai-widgets</tags>
    <rigor-level>FULL</rigor-level>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Event-type definitions consumed by workspace tab manager + assistant + context pane; reverse-flow contract correctness gates the tri-directional model.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C-G2</parallel-group>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Add the following additive event types on the existing `workspace` channel of
    PaneEventBus (per ADR-030 — additive types only on existing channel; NO 5th channel):
    `workspace.user_selection`, `workspace.tab_edited`, `workspace.tab_focused`,
    `workspace.tab_provenance_clicked`.

    These reverse-flow events let the workspace dispatch state changes that the assistant
    + context pane consume. Payloads carry deterministic IDs only (tabId, sessionId,
    columnId, etc.). User-selection MAY carry a brief `selectionText` field (necessary
    for "what does the user have selected?" agent prompts) — but it MUST be capped at
    a reasonable length (200 chars) and the field MUST be flagged in JSDoc as
    user-visible-by-design (different from ADR-015 telemetry-prohibited content). The
    `tab_provenance_clicked` event lets users navigate back to the originating chat
    message or playbook node.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior TypeScript engineer familiar with PaneEventBus contract + reverse-flow event
    design patterns.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Four new event variants on `workspace` channel. Type-check passes. JSDoc cites FR-38.
    Consumers can import + handle.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6/plan.md</file>
